comments: Bogdanovic (DET) establishes himself in Williams's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Bogdanovic (DET) and Williams (CHI) engage and separate, and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
Vucevic (CHI) places a resting forearm on Ivey's (DET) body, and marginal contact occurs as he releases his pass at the end of his drive.
LaVine (CHI) establishes himself in Diallo's (DET) path and does not deliver contact.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Joseph's (DET) path with his arm slightly extended and marginal contact occurs as Joseph defends over the pick.
Joseph (DET) is moving alongside DeRozan's (CHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during DeRozan's drive.
Vucevic (CHI) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Wiseman (DET) maintains vertical arms and absorbs the marginal contact from Williams (CHI) to his side during Williams' shot attempt.
Williams (CHI) and Joseph (DET) both move toward the loose ball when marginal contact occurs.
Diallo (DET) establishes himself in Beverley's (CHI) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
LaVine (CHI) places his hand to Bogdanovic's (DET) side and marginal body contact occurs during his drive to the basket.
LaVine (CHI) moves into Bogdanovic's (DET) space and affects his upward shooting motion.
Vucevic (CHI) and Wiseman (DET) mutually engage and separate as they move toward the rebound.
Diallo (DET) and DeRozan (CHI) come together and separate during the off-ball screen, and the contact is marginal.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Diallo's (DET) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Vucevic (CHI) is imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
LaVine (CHI) is moving alongside Ivey's (DET) path and marginal body contact occurs during Ivey's drive.
Joseph (DET) initiates contact with LaVine's (CHI) arm prior to his gather, and the contact affects LaVine's SQBR.
Caruso (CHI) and Bogdanovic (DET) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Joseph (DET) establishes himself in Beverley's (CHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Wiseman (DET) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Caruso (CHI) legally contests Ivey's (DET) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Diallo (DET) closes out and contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt, and marginal contact occurs after DeRozan's release.
Ivey (DET) signals for and calls a timeout when DET does not have any timeouts remaining.
Joseph (DET) establishes himself in Vucevic's (CHI) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Wiseman (DET) is firming up in Caruso's (CHI) path when marginal body contact occurs on the off-ball screen.
Diallo (DET) and LaVine (CHI) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
DeRozan (CHI) establishes himself in Joseph's (DET) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Joseph (DET) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
Beverley (CHI) legally contests Joseph's (DET) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Diallo (DET) extends two hands toward Vucevic (CHI) and attempts to commit a take foul after he has already passed the ball, and the contact is marginal.
